  <fr:p>We proceed by induction on the <fr:link
href="erct-001F.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001F">truncation level</fr:link> <fr:tex>n</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
  <fr:ol><fr:li>
      When <fr:tex>n=-2</fr:tex>, we recall from <fr:ref
addr="erct-001N"
href="erct-001N.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref> that being <fr:link
href="erct-001H.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001H">contractible</fr:link> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link>.
    </fr:li>
    <fr:li>
      When <fr:tex>n=-1</fr:tex>, we recall from <fr:ref
addr="erct-001O"
href="erct-001O.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref> that
      being a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link>.
    </fr:li>
    <fr:li>
      For <fr:tex>n \geq  0</fr:tex>, we assume by induction that being <html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex>n-1</fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link> to prove that being <html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex>n</fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link>. In other words, we must show that <fr:tex>\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y:A}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y:A}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y:A}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y:A}\right )\mathclose {}}}\mathsf {isTruncated}\,\mathopen {}\left ({n-1}\right )\mathclose {}\,A</fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link>. By our inductive hypothesis, this is a dependent product of <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">propositions</fr:link> (<fr:ref
addr="erct-001B"
href="erct-001B.xml"
taxon="Corollary"></fr:ref>).
    </fr:li></fr:ol>
